The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Saturday, August 09, 2003 				 Teachers punished
																								Bolpur, Aug. 8: Three teachers were beaten up inside a bus in retaliation for pulling up a student who was disturbing class, reports our correspondent.																								Gautam Mondal, a teacher of Ilambazar High School, had punished Pradip Dhibor of Class IX. Pradip complained about his humiliation to relatives and neighbours who targeted Mondal. They stopped the bus in which the teacher was travelling with his colleagues and assaulted them yesterday. 																								The police officer in charge of Ilambazar said three persons have been arrested.
